[A multi-state outbreak of measles linked to non-immune
anthroposophic communities in Austria, Germany, and Norway occurred
earlier in the year and has been described in detail in the
ProMED-mail archived reports referenced below. It will be interesting
to establish whether there is any link between the index case of The
Netherlands outbreak and the outbreaks in these other European
countries and to establish whether the D8 measles genotype is present
all these countries.

The current Netherlands outbreak once again highlights the need to
elevate and maintain the level of acceptance of MMR vaccination
throughout Europe.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of The Netherlands showing
the location of The Hague (Den Haag) can be accessed at:
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=52.2,5.6,6>.
- Mod.CP]
